    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-07-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-06-03T15:08:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) make permanent provisions allowing the expensing of environmental remediation costs; (2) revise the definition of &quot;qualified contaminated site&quot; to include toxic as well as hazardous substances; (3) include within the definition of &quot;hazardous or toxic substances&quot; extremely hazardous substances, as defined by Federal law, and petroleum contaminants; and (4) eliminate the recapture of the expensing deduction upon the sale of environmental remediation property.]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to expand the expensing of environmental remediation costs.</title>
